Caspar David Friedrich (5 September 1774 ‚Äì 7 May 1840) was a 19th-century German Romantic landscape painter, generally considered the most important German artist of his generation. He is best known for his mid-period allegorical landscapes which typically feature contemplative figures silhouetted against night skies, morning mists, barren trees or Gothic or megalithic ruins. His primary interest as an artist was the contemplation of nature, and his often symbolic and anti-classical work seeks to convey a subjective, emotional response to the natural world. Friedrich's paintings characteristically set a human presence in diminished perspective amid expansive landscapes, reducing the figures to a scale that ... directs "the viewer's gaze towards their metaphysical dimension".

description text: Start at Schloss Ranzow golf course and walk along the cliffs to Sassnitz. Mostly level walk with some stairs thru forests with views of the cliffs and beaches. At Sassnitz take a short walk on the beach before returning to Schloss Ranzow via the forest. There are buses at the interpretation center and at Sassnitz trailhead.

In Hagen you have to leave your car at the paid parking. To leave the cycle way as soon as possible, you take a small path to the left just after crossing the road. The next kilometers are very quiet in the forest until you reach the cycle way again. Soon you reach the cliffs where you follow the path above the cliffs to the right. In the Gorge of the Pirates ("Piratenshlucht") you descend to the shore. You can follow the coast line under the cliffs to the north. Avoid high tide because there a few narrow stretches between the sea and the cliffs (see e.g. https://nl.tideschart.com/Germany/Mecklenburg--Vorpommern/Sassnitz/Weekly/ ). To avoid falling rocks, you should also avoid rainy or windy days. We walked there in the late afternoon and had to pass a flock ¬± 50 swans on the shore at a distance of ¬± 2 meters. Luckily they weren't aggressive and didn't react. There aren't much options to leave the shore and climb towards the path above the cliffs. Where we left the shore, it's not an official path, but it isn't difficult nor long. Soon you reach the official and more crowded path above the cliffs. Easy paths will guide you to your car.

The first part you walk beneath the cliffs. In the beginning you can still choose to walk along the shoreline or on a more comfortable path a few meters inland. Therefore you should also avoid rainy or windy days. Anyway, don't forget to enjoy this beautiful walk ! Half way you leave the shore and climb to the official path above the cliffs. In Putgarten you have to leave your car at the paid parking at the entrance of the village. Unless you have a special authorization you can't drive further in the village. After leaving the parking you walk in the main street of Putgarten. After ¬± 800 m you turn right. This street (Vitter Weg) will lead you to the small fishing village of Vitt. Just before the village there is a chapel which you can visit. In Vitt the normal path is above the cliffs. To see more of the coast and to avoid the crowd we followed the shore underneath the cliffs. Avoid high tide (see e.g. https://nl.tideschart.com/Germany/Mecklenburg--Vorpommern/Glowe/ ). To avoid falling rocks, you should also avoid rainy or windy days. There's only one somewhat difficult part. You'll come accross a paved dike : see the third picture (in the distance) and the fourth picture. If it's dry and you feel comfortable, you can just follow this dike. After a short while the dike becomes more steep. If you don't feel comfortable here anymore you can climb to the bush where you'll find a small path. In the bush you'll also find the remains of an old staircase (see waypoint). It's in a bad shape, so you shouldn't follow it. When you see the staircase, the dike has already become somewhat less steep and it's advised to follow here the dike again. Beyond this point, there aren't any difficulties anymore. The more people you'll see, the closer you come to a second parking which you can reach using a staircase in good shape. From that parking you can return by following the combined cycling & walking path above the cliffs till you reach the 2 light houses. From there you follow the main road back to the centre of Putgarten and the parking.
